Storyline:

Kirk gets to return to the planet where, 13 years earlier as a young lieutenant,
he conducted his first planetary survey. The natives live a simple existence with
little or no technology to speak of. Bows and arrows are their main weaponry.
When Kirk, Spock and McCoy beam down, they find a rival tribe now has flintlock
muskets, centuries ahead of normal development. With Spock badly wounded
and taken back to the Enterprise, Kirk and McCoy must see if Klingons have been
upsetting the planet's natural development, but Kirk is attacked and poisoned by
a Mugatu, and it's up to the wife of his old friend Tyree to save him. She's an
ambitious, opportunistic "witch" woman who heals Kirk, also ensnaring his soul.
